The crossover you didn‚Äôt know you needed. The Seattle Aquarium and Nintendo of America are teaming up to bring the Animal Crossing: New Horizons game to life! üåäüçÉ

Beginning October 7, guests can enjoy an AnimalXem th√™m Crossing: New Horizons themed Aquarium experience with photo opportunities, standees of some of your favorite characters, a bingo scavenger hunt and more‚Äîall while learning about our mission: Inspiring Conservation of Our Marine Environment!

This is the first time an aquarium experience like this is available in North America and we‚Äôre giving our members an early look at the excitement on opening weekend! Learn all about it here: https://www.seattleaquarium.org/press-room/critter-crossover-seattle-aquarium-nintendo-team-bring-animal-crossing-new-horizons

Additional themed activities are coming soon. Follow along to stay up to date!

text:
Assemble a group of unlikely heroes when Super Mario RPG releases for Nintendo Switch on Nov. 17! Check out how you can take on a variety of quirky foes using new features, including post-game boss rematches.

Pre-order today: http://ninten.do/61839eIdW

Call it the Switch DS or Nintendo DS Pro. Imagine a Switch/
Nintendo DS like system with enhanced joy-cons, quality buttons, pressure triggers, wider joysticks with enhanced precision and drift-free verified. Enhanced stylus, camera returning with gyroscopic controls remaining. All while keeping our same Nintendo Accounts.

Perhaps they can bring Augmented Reality back similar to the 3D effect but instead using a different method with the camera but this is just an idea.

The system itself would be similar to the Switch but actually have a compact foldable phone sized screen that opens and closes like the 3ds and possibly can be detached for unique gameplay experiences.

The top screen essentially would be a device equal to a standard android phone yet fully designed for the "Switch DS" and needs to be connected back to the system for recharging, updates, etc. Just like a Joy-Con. It serves as an attachable bluetooth device.

(The detachable part is up for discussion but it would be interesting if the system was docked and the second screen was powerful as an android device but can be detached and used for interactive game experiences like a mini map or as a controller for unique tools and abilities in game using the touch screen. Or dare to imagine launching a separate game entirely! [Perhaps have limited access to the gaming library but could be for siblings or friends to launch simple games with the seconds screen or have it interactive somehow]
Possible even a way to make co-op 2 player like games. It would create a 2 in one mobile gaming like experience)

That being said, the detachable screen is nearly an optional feature will surely be optimized and created to be mainly played all together as one device.

Perhaps when docked, The dock could be designed where the top screen is aligned with the TV somehow facing the player or able to remove and use as a extension of your controller or like I mentioned earlier co-op like gameplay experiences.

Overall with this format they can revive our 3DS and Nintendo Switch gaming libraries (perhaps Wii and WiiU but less likely) All that and still barely scratching the surface of its capabilities. As they introduce new ways of playing HD Nintendo games but with more power than the Switch and more ways to play using all the new and returning features from Joy-cons and motion controls, stylus and camera feature returning, and the all new feature of the second screen.

It's pretty much a Switch and DS put together but compact and clean.
